text: The prices are inflated about 10-20% but the location is nice and the staff has always been friendly. The food is good but it doesn't stand out from other restaurants in a similar price range. I'd like to see their bar prices come down to …More

name: A
text: Great pizza and excellent service! We had a group and most had never visited Brixx before. Our waiter was very knowledgeable about the menu items and had great recommendations about food and alcohol pairings. Service was quick and the food was delicious. Great setting and atmosphere, as well!

name: Eddie Yehia
text: Great waitress. Dolly was her named. She knew about every item one the menu and made great recommendations about each item, like get this pizza crispy, get this dipping sauce with your order, she deff earned her tip. And the pizza was great too. I'm surprised it wasn't busier on a Friday night.

name: Dom Howard
text: The  food I ordered was a chicken Alfredo and I ate maybe 3 or 4 bites. The sauce was scare and mediocre (I’ve had better from Walmart), flooded with mushrooms and some half shredded half grilled chicken sprinkled scarcely across the meal. …More

name: Deebra Rogers
text: Nice atmosphere, super clean, and kid friendly. We went on a Sunday afternoon with friends. I had pasta and my husband had pizza. We really enjoyed the food and the service was outstanding. We will be back for sure.

name: Meetal Shah
text: Really disappointing gluten free pizza Margherita. Want my money back. $13 for an undercooked pizza - feel cheated.

name: Renee B
text: Good pies and beer selection. Raleigh Hell Yes Ma'am Belgian Ale and Walnut pear gorgonzola pie were lovely.  For non-alcoholic, caffeine and gluten free seekers - Weeping Radish root beer is the real deal - sarsaparilla forward with creamy vanilla finish and a touch of honey.

name: Ralph Radford
text: Was recommended highly by from a friend of mine. We were not impressed. The app was better than the pizzas. Atmosphere was nice and the staff was great. Probably will not go back.

name: Aaron Mcclain
text: Great pizza!!!! Salads and sandwiches... It might take you a while to get your food because they are always busy. I suggest you call in and order... Then pick up your awesomely prepared food!

name: Will Kaufmann
text: Great food and great location. I think the phone number listed is no longer in service though - we could not get through. The same phone number is posted on Google, Yelp, and the Brixx website.

name: Randy Earl
text: I just had my first dining experience at Brixx and enjoyed it. Yes, I'm the kind of guy who goes to a pizza place and orders the turkey wrap... But, I was pleasantly surprised by what I received! It was filled with generous chunks of real …More

text: We loved it! Those rosemary garlic wings with the gorgonzola dipping sauce...amazing!

name: Steven Walton
text: Went in on a Friday during lunch. I would have expected it to be busier, but, I can't complain.  Just like the other locations the pizza was good and the staff is friendly.  We also had a very short wait time since they weren't busy. …More

name: Greg Scopel
text: Pizza was hot and cooked to perfection... not burnt!  Friendly and cordial staff.  Great overall experience.

name: Lupe Granillo
text: Pretty cool place! Pizza here is just awesome. We stopped by after work here and had very great time chatting and eating their yammy things.

name: Everette Winslow
text: It's pizza. It isn't fancy, it isn't great, it isn't special, but it does the job. I've been there six or seven times and walk away feeling like I just ate pizza. It is a bit more upscale than a "pizza joint," but it isn't cusine. So don't complain that it didn't knock your socks off.

name: Travis M.
text: Amazing pizza, one of the best tasting pizzas I've ever had. One negative: there is only one size and it's not very big in my opinion. I could eat a whole one by myself. The staff is very polite and professional. Definitely will be returning to this location.

name: Sanda Markovic
text: My food was good but I was disappointed with the level of service. I came to eat here on my lunch break during the week. In the entire restaurant there was one busy table (3 people) and me. My server was Abbie and she didn’t even bother to …More

text: Great pizza, after 10pm buy one get one pizza and appetizers. Good for chilling and grabbing a drink.

name: Stan Cope
text: Overall a very good experience.  We had a large group, and the waitress did a great job of keeping on top of a ton of drinks and food.  The food was good.  Did have to send one pie back, but since we ordered like 50, that's understandable. …More

name: Samantha Vaughn
text: This was my first time at this location. Used to always love going to the one in Greensboro. Some coworkers and I went for lunch one day. I was very excited they have a half pizza, half salad special. Perfect amount for lunch. We may have found our new go-to for lunch outings!

name: Krysta Messier
text: Love this place! Daily specials and 50% BOGO anytime after 10pm at night on weekdays and 11pm on weekends. I always go with my roommate and we split a salad and pizza. Saves a little money and we get more food to try! I leave the place full …More

text: This place was great. The pizza was delicious, they cook it right in front of you. Definitely on the medium range of price, but worth it!

text: We had our daughters graduation lunch at Brixx Cameron Village.  We could not have been more pleased.  Cameron Barber-Jones, Manager and his staff exceeded every expectation.  Everything was flawless.  Thank you for such a wonderful experience!!
